-- Bank of Canada Buys C$755 Million of Securities for One Day
-- B y   G r e g   Q u i n n
-- 2013-04-02T18:44:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-02/bank-of-canada-buys-c-755-million-of-securities-for-one-day-1-.html
The Bank of  Canada  bought C$755
million ($744 million) of securities for one day.  The central bank announced the second round of purchases,
aimed to keep overnight lending rates close to its current
target of 1 percent, on its website today from Ottawa. Earlier
the bank said it bought C$485 million.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Greg Quinn in Ottawa at 
 gquinn1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
